113	/**
114	 * Centralised audit emitter for controllers.
115	 *
116	 * Wraps `logAction` so call sites don't have to:
117	 *   - thread the actor id manually,
118	 *   - look up the current request id,
119	 *   - or remember to swallow errors so audit failures never break requests.
120	 *
121	 * Usage from a controller:
122	 *
123	 *     await audit(req, 'resource.create', 'resource', resource.id, { name });
124	 *
125	 * The `req` argument provides the actor (req.user!.userId) so we never log
126	 * mutations performed by anonymous routes (caller is responsible for not
127	 * calling this on public endpoints).
